{"type":"message","id":"e016df7c","parentId":"3f9edcdd","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:36:45.262Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_14f8j2soj9lr_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 153621\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiment (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent findings:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE - Architecture cross-analysis and integration spec done\r\n2. Gap-Decay Synthesis complete\r\n3. CFI Compression Experiment complete with key findings about:\r\n   - CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is too aggressive\r\n   - Constant format problem (tokens like \"for next instantiation\" with freq=160, CFI=1.00)\r\n   - Need three-dimensional filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n   - Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring\r\n\r\nThe next pending action is clearly defined:\r\n- **Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)**\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nThis is a concrete, specific action that advances the goals. I should:\r\n1. Create a script to run this experiment\r\n2. Update the pulse script to include this experiment\r\n3. Or create a new experiment script\r\n\r\nLet me think about what file to edit. The most direct action would be to:\r\n1. Create an experiment script for the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Or modify the existing pulse script to run this experiment\r\n\r\nGiven the \"prefer file edits\" instruction and the need to actually run the experiment, I should create or modify something that will execute this experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a new experiment script for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression experiment revealed the \"constant format problem\" - tokens with high frequency AND high CFI are metaprogramming artifacts, not meaningful research content. The next step is clearly defined: test hybrid scoring formula that should distinguish constant-format (freq≈160, CFI=1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate experiment script for Strategy C (Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring) that implements the formula score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120) and runs comparison against binary thresholds on the 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\n## Experiment Definition\r\nTest hypothesis: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes:\r\n- **Constant format** (freq≈160, CFI=1): score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (but should be penalized by freq cap)\r\n- **Research trajectory** (freq<120, CFI>0.5): score = 0.7 × 0.95 = 0.665\r\n\r\nWait - the formula as stated gives 1.0 for constant format, which doesn't help.\r\n\r\n## Revised Formula\r\nNeed to penalize constant repetition while rewarding meaningful patterns:\r\n\r\n**score(T) = CFI(T) × sigmoid((freq(T) - 80) / 40)**\r\n\r\nThis:\r\n- Penalizes freq > 80 (decay beyond optimal)\r\n- Rewards freq in range [40, 120] \r\n- CFI still filters noise\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nSee: `experiments/cfi_hybrid_scoring.py`\r\nfile: experiments/cfi_hybrid_scoring.py\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 15:36:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381005260}}
{"type":"message","id":"3feb8e47","parentId":"e016df7c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:36:47.391Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also read the actual mutation file and the Python experiment script that was created.","thinkingSignature":"8112b9fbba27ed33fc2b9eddfab9b3b9a7a0abaeb683c6823c8fc6c97d929efe"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_copdsayz42ce_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 153621.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3136,"output":73,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15454,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774381005262}}
{"type":"message","id":"655bc5a9","parentId":"3feb8e47","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:36:47.397Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_copdsayz42ce_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"experiments/cfi_hybrid_scoring.py\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n\n## Experiment Definition\nTest hypothesis: `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes:\n- **Constant format** (freq≈160, CFI=1): score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (but should be penalized by freq cap)\n- **Research trajectory** (freq<120, CFI>0.5): score = 0.7 × 0.95 = 0.665\n\nWait - the formula as stated gives 1.0 for constant format, which doesn't help.\n\n## Revised Formula\nNeed to penalize constant repetition while rewarding meaningful patterns:\n\n**score(T) = CFI(T) × sigmoid((freq(T) - 80) / 40)**\n\nThis:\n- Penalizes freq > 80 (decay beyond optimal)\n- Rewards freq in range [40, 120] \n- CFI still filters noise\n\n## Implementation\nSee: `experiments/cfi_hybrid_scoring.py`\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381007395}}
