{"type":"message","id":"95c99fb3","parentId":"e575e3ba","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:37:00.356Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_gw1ltkkew8md_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"commit 66869726919e92d51330f3de60b5716689af2788\nAuthor: Sandbox <sandbox@breakaway>\nDate:   Tue Mar 24 15:36:36 2026 -0400\n\n    pulse: 2026-03-24 153621\n\n .llm_prompt.txt                                    |  54 ++++----\n .llm_response.txt                                  | 154 +++++++--------------\n .mutation_parse_result.json                        |   4 +-\n memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 153621.md          |  76 ++++++++++\n mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 153621.mutation      |  25 ++++\n .../2026-03-24 153522.mutation                     |   0\n 6 files changed, 178 insertions(+), 135 deletions(-)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":633,"aggregated":"commit 66869726919e92d51330f3de60b5716689af2788\nAuthor: Sandbox <sandbox@breakaway>\nDate:   Tue Mar 24 15:36:36 2026 -0400\n\n    pulse: 2026-03-24 153621\n\n .llm_prompt.txt                                    |  54 ++++----\n .llm_response.txt                                  | 154 +++++++--------------\n .mutation_parse_result.json                        |   4 +-\n memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 153621.md          |  76 ++++++++++\n mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 153621.mutation      |  25 ++++\n .../2026-03-24 153522.mutation                     |   0\n 6 files changed, 178 insertions(+), 135 deletions(-)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774381020354}}
{"type":"message","id":"b0f93778","parentId":"95c99fb3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:37:09.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me compile a summary of what happened in this pulse.\n\nKey things that happened:\n1. The pulse ran and analyzed the state (CFI Compression experiment findings)\n2. It identified the \"constant format problem\" - tokens with high freq AND high CFI are metaprogramming artifacts\n3. Proposed a new formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × sigmoid((freq(T) - 80) / 40)\n4. Created a mutation to create `experiments/cfi_hybrid_scoring.py`\n5. The mutation is in \"proposed\" state (not yet applied)\n6. Previous mutation was moved from proposed to rejected\n\n\n7. The previous experiment (pulse_153522) is now rejected since the constant format problem undermines that approach","thinkingSignature":"a651063eff4cc90938d6040a78b2ab925c775a166ef1cad60074df9dbff7b27d"},{"type":"text","text":"## Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 15:36\n\n**CFI Compression findings are in.** The experiment revealed a critical flaw in the binary threshold approach:\n\n- **The \"constant format problem\":** Tokens with `freq≈160` AND `CFI=1.0` (e.g., \"for next instantiation\") are **metaprogramming artifacts**, not research content — but they score perfectly under CFI×threshold strategies.\n- Binary thresholds (CFI ≥ 0.5, freq ∈ [3, 120)) help but don't solve the root issue.\n\n**Next step identified:** A hybrid scoring formula was proposed:\n```\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × sigmoid((freq(T) - 80) / 40)\n```\nThis penalizes over-frequency (decay past 80) while rewarding tokens in the research-trajectory sweet spot [40–120].\n\n**Mutation proposed:** `experiments/cfi_hybrid_scoring.py` — not yet applied, pending approval.\n\n**Previous mutation rejected:** The earlier Strategy B mutation (CFI≥0.5 AND freq∈[3,120)) was moved to `mutations/rejected/` since the constant-format problem undermines that approach too.\n\n**Git status:** 6 files changed, one new session log, one proposed mutation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4222,"output":437,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16904,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774381020356}}
